{{Quote|Your condition gives you a temporary reprieve from these marching orders, Master Devan, though I fully expect you are opting for the same choice Master Lanius and the rest of the Academy staff have made personally.''"<br />"''What &hellip; what choice?''"<br />"''The Right of Denial, of course. I would beg you to reconsider, but I doubt you would hear me.|Darrus Jeht and Devan For'deschel|<ref name="Marching Orders" />}}
The '''Right of Denial''' was a [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] tradition that allowed members of the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] to protest against a decision made by the [[Jedi High Council/Legends|Jedi Council]], the Order's governing body. During the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], the right was invoked by the Jedi instructors of the [[Almas Academy]], a [[Jedi academy]] that was located on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Almas]], after the Council attempted to conscript them to fight in the conflict.

==Description==
{{Quote|I didn't just walk away from the Order&mdash;I didn't exercise Right of Denial. I stopped being a Jedi.|Bardan Jusik, on his resignation from the Jedi Order|<ref name="Revelation">''[[Legacy of the Force: Revelation]]''</ref>}}
The Right of Denial was a tradition followed by the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] that, when invoked, allowed a [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] to protest against an order from the [[Jedi High Council/Legends|Jedi Council]],<ref name="Marching Orders" /> the Order's governing body.<ref name="The Jedi Path">[[The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force (real-life book)|''The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force'']]</ref> The right was rarely used, and, by the [[Time/Legends|time]] of the waning [[Standard year/Legends|years]] of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]], entreating the Right of Denial was considered to be almost [[Treason/Legends|treasonous]]. Jedi who invoked the right had to hand in their [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsabers]] to the Order, as possessing such a weapon while still protesting a Council decision was a criminal offense. Additionally, the individuals were stripped of their legal authority, leaving them as Jedi in name only. Calling upon the Right of Denial was not regarded as a denouncement of the Jedi Order; rather, it was only an act of contempt against the Jedi Council and not the [[Jedi Code/Legends|Jedi Code]],<ref name="Marching Orders" /> the guiding principles of the Order.<ref name="The Jedi Path" />

==History==
{{Quote|I will be on my ship, awaiting the last of the Jedi here &hellip; or their lightsabers.|Darrus Jeht, on the Almas Jedi|<ref name="Marching Orders" />}}
During the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]],<ref name="Conflict and Mastery">{{Wizards|url=default.asp?x=starwars/livingforce/swlf20040311|text=Conflict and Mastery|int=Conflict and Mastery}}</ref> a [[The galaxy/Legends|galactic]] conflict that was fought between the Republic and the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]],<ref name="TCWCG">''[[The Clone Wars Campaign Guide]]''</ref> the Jedi Council sent [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Darrus Jeht/Legends|Darrus Jeht]] to the [[Almas Academy]], a [[Jedi academy|Jedi teaching facility]] located on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Almas]] in the [[Cularin system/Legends|Cularin system]], to call up some of the Academy's staff to fight in the war.<ref name="Conflict and Mastery" /> Later in the conflict, the Council sent Jeht back to the Academy to conscript the school's remaining [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knights]] and Jedi Masters. However, [[Lanius Qel-Bertuk]]&mdash;the Almas Academy's headmaster&mdash;and the rest of the Academy's staff, including the [[Jedi artisan/Legends|Jedi artisan]] [[Felanil Baaks]], protested and invoked the Right of Denial, handing in their lightsabers to Jeht. Jeht went to the Academy's infirmary and spoke with<ref name="Marching Orders" /> the Academy's [[Mistress of Lightsabers]],<ref name="Devan">{{Wizards|url=default.asp?x=starwars/livingforce/swlf20030619devan|text=Devan}}</ref> [[Devan For'deschel]], who was recovering from surgery on her [[Limb/Legends|arm]], and he informed her of the other instructors' invocation of the right. For'deschel was surprised by their decision and began considering whether to invoke the Right of Denial herself.<ref name="Marching Orders" />

Jeht subsequently departed Almas, and Qel-Bertuk's lightsaber was sent to [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]],<ref name="Marching Orders" /> the world on which the Jedi Council was based,<ref name="The Jedi Path" /> as a protest.<ref name="Marching Orders" /> The implementation of the Right of Denial left the Almas Jedi without a right of representation on Coruscant and meant that the Republic no longer considered the Almas Academy to be an active Jedi academy. As a result, Jeht placed the Cularin [[Star system/Legends|system]] under martial law, in accordance with the terms of the [[Emergency Powers Act/Legends|Emergency Powers Act]].<ref name="Marching Orders" />

In circa [[21 BBY/Legends|21 BBY]],<ref name="TC date">''[[Republic Commando: True Colors]]'' states that Bardan Jusik resigned from the Jedi Order 547 days after the [[First Battle of Geonosis/Legends|Battle of Geonosis]], which is dated to [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]] by ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''. This thus dates his resignation to circa 21 BBY.</ref> the Jedi Knight [[Bardan Jusik]] resigned from the Jedi Order as a protest against the Jedi Council's sanctioning of the use of [[Clone trooper/Legends|clone troopers]], [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Soldier/Legends|soldiers]] who were [[Cloning/Legends|bred]] on the planet [[Kamino/Legends|Kamino]], in the war against the Confederacy, because he believed that the Jedi were treating the clones as [[Slavery/Legends|slaves]].<ref name="True Colors">''[[Republic Commando: True Colors]]''</ref> However, Jusik [[41 ABY|later]] told the Jedi Knight [[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina Solo]] that when he left the Order, he had not invoked the Right of Denial and had instead ceased to be a Jedi.<ref name="Revelation" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Right of Denial was created by [[August Hahn|August]] and [[Cynthia Hahn]] and featured in ''[[Marching Orders]]'', a short story that was published on [[Wizards.com]] in [[2005]] as a supplement to the [[Living Force (roleplaying campaign)|''Living Force'']] [[Star Wars Roleplaying Game|roleplaying]] campaign.<ref name="Marching Orders" /> Participants of the ''Living Force'' campaign [[Roleplaying game|roleplay]] as player-created characters,<ref name="LFCG">''[[Living Force Campaign Guide]]''</ref> and ''Marching Orders'' gives Jedi player characters the choice of leaving Almas with Jeht, or exercising the Right of Denial and remaining in the Cularin system. Those who choose to utilize the right send their lightsabers to Coruscant and are eventually given replacement lightsabers by Felanil Baaks.<ref name="Marching Orders" />

